Open Library edition records may not always contain an `authors` array (e.g., for anonymous works, edited volumes, or records with incomplete metadata). The current implementation strictly asserts that `edition.authors` is a non-empty array, which will cause the entire ISBN resolution process to crash for any book without a listed author.

We should gracefully handle the absence of authors by returning an empty array.

```javascript
export function editionAuthorKeys(edition) {
  if (!edition.authors || !Array.isArray(edition.authors)) {
    return [];
  }
  return edition.authors
    .filter(author => author && typeof author.key === 'string' && author.key.length > 0)
    .map(author => author.key);
}
```

![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The current implementation strictly asserts that `authors.length > 0`, which will cause the ISBN resolver to fail for any book that does not have a primary author. To make the resolver more robust, we should make the `author` field optional in the generated BibTeX entry.

```suggestion
export function bookBibTeX({ isbn, title, authors, publisher, year }) {
  const fields = [
    ['title', title],
    ...(authors.length > 0 ? [['author', authors.join(' and ')]] : []),
    ['publisher', publisher],
    ['year', year],
    ['isbn', isbn],
  ];
  const body = fields.map(([name, value]) => `  
${name} = {
${value}}`).join(',\n');
  return `@book{isbn_
${isbn},\n
${body}\n}`;
}
```

