If `localStorage` contains an invalid or corrupted theme preference, `AppThemeSchema.parse` will throw a ZodError and crash the application on startup. Using `safeParse` with a fallback to `DEFAULT_APP_THEME` prevents startup crashes.

```suggestion
function readStoredTheme(): AppTheme {
  const storedTheme = localStorage.getItem(THEME_STORAGE_KEY);
  if (storedTheme === null) {
    return DEFAULT_APP_THEME;
  }
  const parsed = AppThemeSchema.safeParse(storedTheme);
  return parsed.success ? parsed.data : DEFAULT_APP_THEME;
}
```

